                            <comment id="446832" author="ys" created="Thu, 6 Mar 2025 03:08:45 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I have looked through the many kind of &quot;wait delete timed out&quot; error cases. Seems they all have logs:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;
Delete is not completed in 28 seconds
CMD: trevis-101vm6 /usr/sbin/lctl get_param osc.*MDT*.sync_*
osc.lustre-OST0000-osc-MDT0000.sync_changes=0
osc.lustre-OST0000-osc-MDT0000.sync_in_flight=0
osc.lustre-OST0000-osc-MDT0000.sync_in_progress=1
osc.lustre-OST0000-osc-MDT0002.sync_changes=0
osc.lustre-OST0000-osc-MDT0002.sync_in_flight=0

&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This indicted a osp request stuck in commit phase. I think we should add a some debug code in test script to figure out why it was delayed. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
